        <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444]">
          In the early 90s, things at AB started to climb again — mainly because a group of talented players who had played for the club for many years chose to stay and rebuild AB, even though they were offered lucrative deals to join other top-flight clubs. These players valued the camaraderie and special spirit of AB more than the money on offer elsewhere. Three players in particular deserve a mention: René Henriksen, who made his Danish national team debut at the age of 28, Peter Frandsen, and Peter Rasmussen — who holds the club record at AB with 394 appearances, just 2 more than Peter Frandsen.
        </p>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-8 clear-both">
