          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#111]">
            The effort came close to succeeding, but in the end the club had to admit that the big bet hadn't paid off. A few years followed in which AB's squad consisted of part-time professionals. Three seasons followed in which the club secured its survival in the very last round of matches. There was euphoria every time, with some great late-season finishes, and it seemed AB was destined to survive.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#111] mt-5">
            In the 2014/15 season, however, things went wrong. After another great final push, AB lost the last game and were relegated to the 2nd Division. It was a quick return to the 1st Division for the Academics, who, after a mixed autumn, played fantastic football in the spring, winning 12 of 16 matches and scoring 38 goals. Unfortunately, it wasn't enough, and the following season the club was relegated back to the 2nd Division.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-[calc(1.4rem+18px+1.75rem)]">
