          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-8">
            In November 2023, Sofie Brandi Petersen replaced Erik Stover, who stepped down as CEO. To give his full attention to the sporting side, Chang stepped down as Chairman, and AB A/S board member Brian Grieco was elected Chairman — positions both still hold today.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            AB parted ways with head coach David Roufpanah after just one season. In May 2024, Joey Guðjónsson became the club's new head coach. Guðjónsson has been an assistant coach of the Icelandic national team since 2022 and was named Icelandic Coach of the Year in 2018. He also had an impressive playing career as a central midfielder at the highest level in England, Holland and Spain, including 10 seasons in English football — among them Aston Villa in the Premier League, as well as Wolves and Burnley. He also earned 34 caps for Iceland's senior national team. AB finished the 24/25 season with positive momentum: a 4th-place finish and a record of 14 wins, 9 draws and 9 losses.
          </p>
