          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.15rem] leading-[1.75] text-white/85 mt-5">
            In December 2025, Guðjónsson left the club for family reasons, and AB hired Fannar Berg Gunnólfsson as head coach. He had previously served as an assistant coach under Guðjónsson.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.15rem] leading-[1.75] text-white/85 mt-5">
            In other staffing news, Henrik Bom, former head of the Danish American Chamber of Commerce in New York City, became AB A/S's new President, Head of Commercial, in February 2026, spearheading AB A/S's commercial strategy and revenue growth alongside CEO Sofie Brandi Petersen, forging strategic alliances and partnerships in Denmark and abroad.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.15rem] leading-[1.75] text-white/85 mt-5">
            AB finished the regular season with 4 wins, 2 draws and 0 losses in its final 6 games, and a promotion record of 7 wins and 3 losses. Despite a 2-1 loss to FC Roskilde in round 28, HIK beat third-placed Næstved, securing AB's promotion to the 1st Division with four rounds still to play. And in round 30, against HIK, AB needed just a point to seal the 2nd Division title — AB delivered a commanding 5-0 win to become champions.
          </p>
